- Allows you to use your computer from somewhere else

#+ATTR_REVEAL: :frag (appear)
- Enabled on the Remote tab on the System Properties window
  - ensure that both computers have this enabled
  - identify the target machine by name or IP
  - ~MTSC~ (Microsoft Terminal Services Client)
    - port ... 3389!
    - Well engineered service - can account for bandwidth problems, use local resources
** Home vs. Work vs. Public network settings
- Set when configuring network connection
  - *Home* - allows your shared data to be discoverable by others on network
  - *Work* - Usually implies that a Domain is in use
  - *Public* - Most restrictive
** Firewall settings
- From Control Panel, Search or Run
- Filters web traffic using TCP port numbers
  - Windows Firewall simple, user-friendly, no IPtables
*** Configuration
- Pre-configured rules, usually requires no changes for simple home use
*** Exceptions
- Can make Exceptions on the fly if connectivity problems
  - Done per app
*** Enabling/disabling Windows Firewall
