- IPv4 - 32-bit address
*** Subnet mask
- Identifies the network
  - which of the remaining octets identify the host:
    - e.g. ~255.255.255.0~ three octets for the network, eight bits for the host

*** DNS
- Here, can set the IP address of the DNS server
*** Gateway
- The device that provides access to the Internet
- At your home, probably your router
- Gateway address must be correct on the workstation or it will not be able to connect to the network!
** Network card properties

*** Half duplex/full duplex/auto
- Half-duplex: one way transport of data
- Full-duplex: both ways
- Auto-negotiation: communication between devices

